The paper proposes a neural network architecture for the task of diving classification using video frames as input. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed model also involves attention mechanisms and LSTM-based networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training a neural network, which is a common technique in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
